{
  "texts": [
    "Forward Generation WorkflowThe fundamental concept of AutoBench is to emulate the design process used by human engineers.",
    "As outlined in Fig. 2, the primary generation pipeline is split into two distinct tracks: the driver track and the checker track.",
    "The major steps of the testbench generation workflow in Fig. 3 are explained in detail below.",
    "3.1.1 Circuit Type Discriminator Digital logical circuits are classified into two types: combinational (CMB) circuits and sequential (SEQ) circuits.",
    "The circuit type can be derived from the DUT's description, even without DUT's code."
  ]
}